ion for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def getDecimalValue(self, head: Optional[ListNode]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\n# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def getDecimalValue(self, head: Optional[ListNode]) -> int:\n        # Initialize the result variable to 0\n        result = 0\n        \n        # Traverse the linked list\n        current = head\n        while current:\n            # Shift the current result to the left by 1 (equivalent to multiplying by 2)\n            # and add the current node's value\n            result = (result << 1) | current.val\n            # Move to the next node\n            current = current.next\n        \n        return result\n```\n\nThis solution works by iterating through the linked list and treating it as a binary number. By shifting the accumulated result to the left and adding the current node's value, we effectively convert the binary number represented by the linked list into a decimal number.", "estimated_date": 1576368000000}